  "prompt": "What percentage of commission do sellers need to pay e-commerce websites like Flipkart, eBay, Amazon, Shopclues, Shimply, Myntra etc., when selling clothing such as t-shirts?",
  "response": "The percentage of commission that sellers need to pay to e-commerce websites for selling clothing such as t-shirts can vary depending on the platform, the category of the product, and sometimes the specific agreement between the seller and the platform. Generally, for clothing items like t-shirts:\n\n- **Amazon** typically charges a referral fee that can range from around 10% to 17% depending on the category.\n- **Flipkart** usually charges a commission fee that can range from around 12% to 25%.\n- **eBay** often charges a final value fee that can range from around 10% to 15%.\n- **Myntra** typically charges around 20% to 30% as commission.\n- **Shopclues** commonly charges a commission fee that can range from around 12% to 20%.\n- **Shimply** charges a commission fee which can vary but is typically around 10% to 20%.\n\nThese percentages are approximate and subject to change. Sellers should verify the exact rates and any additional fees (like shipping, payment processing, etc.) on the respective platforms and consider any promotional or seasonal changes that might affect these fees.",
